French term for gawker or bystander Gérard Auliac, Le Badaud, 2002 The badaud is an important urban type from 18th and 19th-century French literature, one that has been adapted to explain aspects of mass culture and modern experience. The term badaud (plural: badauds) comes from the French and has the basic meaning of gawker, or more neutrally, bystander. Ivorian singer Oxxy NorgyBackground informationGenresWorld music, Coupé décaléMusical artist Oxxy Norgy is an Ivorian singer known for his Coupé Décalé style of music. Oxxy Norgy first became known for his numerous features, including those with Boombastic Dj and 4x4 académia. He released his first album, which shared the same name of his initial concept Moto bengué and was inspired by danse de la moto, a derivative of the coupé décalé style.
